# Dyadic Coupled Fluxes Are Exact Only As Aggregations Of The Helical-Triad Ledger

Status: `VERIFIED` exact-core verdict with `INFERRED` dyadic-packaging consequence

For the Step-011 coupled energy-helicity branch, the strongest exact invariant
ledger currently supported on disk stops at the exact Fourier/Leray triad law
with helical-triad conservation constraints.

That means the provisional `dyadic coupled fluxes` package is exact only in
one limited sense: each shell-level energy or helicity transfer entry must be
obtained by summing exact packet-complete helical-triad transfers over the
triads whose roles land in the chosen shell pattern.

So the dyadic ledger is an aggregation of the exact helical-triad core, not a
stronger new invariant and not a pre-frozen coercive shell law.

This is the honest filing because the repository still does not contain a
standalone exact dyadic energy/helicity identity sheet or a theorem-facing
one-sided flux inequality for the frozen package.

